mkdir : creating a directory
mkdir -p a/b/c : creating multiple directories at a time
cd : change directory
cp : copy a file one location to another location
cp -r <dir> <dest> : copy entire directory recursively
ls -- This command lists all the contents in the current working directory
ls –l :-- Using ‘l’ flag, lists all the contents along with its owner settings, permissions & time stamp (long format)
ls –a :-- Using ‘a’ flag, lists all the hidden contents in the specified directory
grep -- This command searches for a particular string/ word in a text file. This is similar to “Ctrl+F” but executed via a CLI
